<HEADLINE> London Shares Close Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Share prices fell Monday on the London stock
Exchange following indications that Friday's resurgence of the
Nasdaq Stock Market in the United States may be short lived.
</P>
<P>
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange-100 share index TSE 100
closed down 36.5 points, or 0.6 percent, at 6,533.4.
</P>
<P>
   Provisional market volume was 1.2 billion shares compared with
1.5 billion on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''There are two key concerns for traders ... over the next few
weeks. The first is whether the current rebound we are seeing in
the Nasdaq is genuine and the second is whether the traditional
stocks can hold their attraction if another wave of panic hits the
market,'' said Brian Kiely, technical strategist at Royal Bank of
Scotland.
</P>
