<DOCNO> APW20000410.0049 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 14:31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Holmes Gets AP Post in Nebraska  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Michael Holmes, correspondent in charge of The
Associated Press' statehouse bureau in Austin, Texas, has been
promoted to chief of bureau for Nebraska, where he worked as a
reporter for two newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Monday by Louis D. Boccardi, AP
president and CEO. Holmes succeeds Paul Simon, who resigned to take
a job in Denver.
</P>
<P>
   Holmes, 49, is a native of Cincinnati and a graduate of the
University of Nebraska at Omaha. He joined the AP in Des Moines,
Iowa, in 1977. Three years later he became the first AP
correspondent in Toledo, Ohio. He was named news editor in
Columbus, Ohio, in 1981 before going to Austin three years later.
</P>
<P>
   Prior to joining AP, Holmes worked as a reporter for the Lincoln
Journal and Star and the Omaha World-Herald.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
