<HEADLINE> Police say Camden man fatally stabs brother in heat of argument  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) -- A Camden man was in jail Monday, a day after
he was arrested in the fatal stabbing of his brother during an
argument in the basement of their Denfield Street home, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   Antone T. Watson, 38, was charged with murder and was being held
in Camden County Jail in lieu of $300,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Antone Watson stabbed his brother, Vincent, 37, in
the chest with a knife at 1:50 a.m. Sunday. Vincent Watson ran
upstairs to the kitchen to get help from his mother, father and
brother, who were all home at the time.
</P>
<P>
   Vincent Watson was pronounced dead at Cooper Hospital-University
Medical Center about two hours later, according to the Camden
County Prosecutor's Office.
</P>
<P>
   Greg Reinert, a spokesman for the prosecutor, would not comment
on the nature of the brothers' argument.
</P>
