<HEADLINE> Canadian Officer Charged in Killing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALGARY (AP) -- A Royal Canadian Mounted Police constable was
charged with second-degree murder Monday in the shooting death of a
suspect killed in a jail cell.
</P>
<P>
   Constable Mike Ferguson entered no plea during a court
appearance in Lethbridge, Alberta, 90 miles southeast of Calgary.
</P>
<P>
   He is accused of shooting Darren John Varley, 26, during a
struggle at an RCMP holding cell in Pincher Creek, 90 miles south
of Calgary, on Oct. 4, 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Varley had been arrested after getting into a fight with a
police officer. A second altercation broke out at the police
holding cell, and Varley was wounded by two gunshots. He died after
being airlifted to a Calgary hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Ferguson's arrest followed an investigation by the RCMP major
crimes unit in Calgary, said chief Supt. Rick Bowlby.
</P>
</TEXT>
