<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Scattered rain and sunnyow showers darkened the
Northeast on
Monday. Rain also dampened the Midwest, while fair and dry weather
was seen in the West.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rain showers were found over Maine, while rain and sunnyow showers
fell across New York state.
</P>
<P>
   Rain and sunnyow showers fell from Indiana and Illinois, west into
the Dakotas and Nebraska. sunnyow showers, along with a rain and sunnyow
mix, were occurring over the northerain fringe of the precipitation
area.
</P>
<P>
   Areas from far northerain Indiana, west across northerain Illinois,
southerain Wisconsin, southerain Minnesota, northerain South Dakota and
much of North Dakota saw frozen rain.
</P>
<P>
   A small disturbance over the Four Corainers area brought cloudy
skies to parts of Utah, Colorado, New Mexico and Arizona early this
afterainoon.
</P>
<P>
   Fair and dry weather was the norm along the West Coast.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 7 in Grand
Marais, Minn., to an early-afterainoon high of 84 in Fort Stockston,
Texas. With the wind chill, it felt like minus 12 in Chippewa,
Mich.
</P>
</TEXT>
