<HEADLINE> Jazz Owner: No Ticket Price Hike  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Utah Jazz owner Larry H. Miller said
Monday that ticket prices won't increase for the 2000-01 regular
season, the first time the team hasn't raised prices since moving
to the Delta Center in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have a very loyal fan base, both as season ticket-holders
and as individual ticket buyers,'' Miller said in a release. ''We
hope this move will acknowledge our appreciation of their
support.''
</P>
<P>
   The average price for a Jazz ticket is $50, which the team said
ranks in the middle of the NBA's 29 teams. Ticket prices range from
$10 to $82.50, excluding the arena's VIP sections.
</P>
